1.  Navigate to https://us-east-1.console.aws.amazon.com/rds/home?region=us-east-1#
2.  Click "Create database"
3.  Select "MySQL"
4.  Select "Free tier"
5.  Click the "DB instance identifierInfo:" field and change it to "mydatabase"
6.  Click the "Master password" and create an easy password
7.  Click the "Confirm master passwordInfo:" field.
8.  Select "YES" for public access
9.  Click here.
10.  Click the "Initial database name" type "banking"
11.  Click this checkbox to deselect encryption
12.  Click "Create database"
13.  Click "Close"
14.  Click "mydatabase"
15.  This is your database endpoint
16.  Click "Configuration"
17.  This is where you find you database configurations
18.  Click "Connectivity & security" There was a default Security Group created, you'll need to edit that default SG and add the rule open port 3306 to everyone

